2. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - The paper studies linear index coding in a cellular network scenario, which is a topic related to networking and internet architecture. 
3. cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) - The paper proposes a new type of side information graph, which is a topic related to social and information networks. 
4. cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) - The paper proposes a new fitting matrix and encoding method, which are topics related to data structures and algorithms. 
5. cs.CC (Computational Complexity) - The paper studies the minimum rank of the proposed fitting matrices, which is a topic related to computational complexity.
